==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Raphany
<hw>Raph"a*ny</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧f"⟦adot⟧*n⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>raphanie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
convulsive disease, attended with ravenous hunger, not uncommon in
Sweden and Germany. It was so called because supposed to be caused by
eating corn with which seeds of jointed charlock (<spn>Raphanus
raphanistrum</spn>) had been mixed, but the condition is now known to be
a form of ergotism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raphe</ent>⟦br⟧
